        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 2:10PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 210 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Fort Lee. These storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

Locations impacted include...
Petersburg, Hopewell, Colonial Heights, Fort Lee, Chester, Prince
George, Ettrick, New Bohemia, Richard Bland College, Birchett
Estate, and Petersburg National Battlefield.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Please report significant weather by calling 757-899-
2415, posting to the NWS Wakefield Facebook page, or using X
@NWSWAKEFIELDVA.</instruction>
